comments.body:
I could easily add WiFI SSID to the dialog text on iOS. More than that, the implementation allows user to put app into background, go to System Preferences to change WiFi point and return back.

Studio can for instance run:
{code}
/System/Library/PrivateFrameworks/Apple80211.framework/Versions/Current/Resources/airport -I | awk '/ SSID/ {print substr($0, index($0, $2))}'
{code}

but there may be issues with Studio when the machine is wired instead.
